N:google-workspace
D:Create, read, update, and manage Google Workspace documents and services through official REST APIs. Use when working with Docs, Sheets, Slides, Drive, Gmail, Calendar, Chat, Forms, Admin SDK, or Apps Script.
G:google-workspace google-docs google-sheets google-slides google-drive gmail google-calendar google-chat google-forms admin-sdk apps-script spreadsheet presentation drive-folder send-email
F:Claude|Gemini|Codex|OpenCode
T:Bash|Read|Write|Edit|Glob|Grep

U[5]:
  Create or edit Google Docs, Sheets, and Slides
  Send Gmail, manage drafts, labels, and mailbox workflows
  Create calendar events, invite attendees, and check schedules
  Upload, organize, and search Google Drive files and folders
  Automate Workspace operations through Apps Script or Admin SDK

S[4]{n,action,details}:
  1,Enable APIs,Enable Workspace APIs in Google Cloud before authenticating credentials
  2,Install Clients,Install google-api-python-client google-auth-httplib2 google-auth-oauthlib
  3,Authenticate,Use OAuth2 for user data or service accounts for backend automation
  4,Execute,Call the product-specific REST API with the official client libraries and required scopes

R[4]:
  Prefer official REST APIs and client SDKs over browser scraping
  Match scopes to the narrowest product access required for the task
  Keep OAuth and service-account secrets outside the repository
  Use batch APIs for large document or spreadsheet updates when available
